  "name": "RPlog_Freezer_Burn",
  "title": "Freezer Burn",
  "summary": "At Hawk's Roost Spaceport on Caspar, Dr. Lynae Cassius returns to her ship the Red Sky to find a hooded, masked figure flanked by two armed mercenaries waiting near her boarding ramp. The figure is Darth Malus, recently thawed from twenty years in carbonite, delivered to her per a message she had not yet read; she dismisses the mercs and brings him aboard to her medbay. While treating his carbonite sickness, blindness, and dehydration, the two engage in a long, sparring philosophical conversation about murder, peace, fear, and the nature of the Sith. Malus probes Lynae's psychological walls and the abandoned research she once pursued: a means to genetically eradicate Force sensitivity, which she gave up as a moral and practical impossibility. Malus tempts her with the idea that anything is possible and that she need only break her chains, reciting the Sith Code, before settling in to meditate as Lynae quietly tidies up and leaves him to recover.",
